BRIEFING:
HNL DEP GATE A14
MILITARY EXERCISE SENTRY ALOHA 1/27-2/12
A MOSTLY DRY NNE FLOW IS DELIVERING VARYING AMOUNTS OF STABLE LOW CLOUDS TO WINDWARD AREAS THIS MORNING, WITH CONDITIONS RANGING FROM CLEAR TO OVERCAST. CLOUD BASES ARE BETWEEN 3 AND 4 KFT, SO PERIODS OF MVFR CIG CAN BE EXPECTED ALONG N AND E FACING SLOPES, ESPECIALLY THIS AFTERNOON OVER KAUAI AS A BAND OF ENHANCED LOW CLOUDS AND LIGHT SHOWERS MOVES IN FROM THE N. THIS BAND WILL LIKELY INCREASE MVFR CIG OVER WINDWARD PORTIONS OF OAHU AND MAUI COUNTY OVERNIGHT.
